  "texts": [
    "More specifically, the activation at each point in time and space, that is, the output of priority computations, signals a quantity proportional to some weighted combination of stipulated influences (→ Guidance).",
    "Points in the maps might represent raw location or they might index something akin to objects (proto-objects; Jeck et al., 2019; Wischnewski et al., 2010).",
    "Because salience and priority maps are derived from visual processing embodied in the representation of the visual field, it is reasonable to assume that they are homeomorphic with the map of the visual field.",
    "Accurate models of these maps should therefore take magnification of the central visual field and other distortions into account.",
    "Variation in resolution of attention deployment across the visual field might be a by-product of visual processing or a distinct feature of the extraretinal processes guiding attention (Hulleman & Olivers, 2017)."
  ],
